<P>
Teledyne Inc.: The aviation, electronics and specialty metals concern reported 
third-quarter income of $9.1 million, down 88% from the same quarter of 1989, 
on revenue of $846.4 million, off 3% from last year. The profit figure for 
1989's third period included $35.2 million for income of discontinued 
operations. The Los Angeles-based firm cited strikes at various plants and cost 
overruns on some defense contracts. 
