Rapping for Free Speech: Rappers 2 Live Crew, Ice Cube, Ice T, N.W.A and the 
Geto Boys have all contributed songs to a new anti-censorship compilation 
titled "Explicit Rap" due out in November on Priority Records. The album's 
artwork features a 12-inch tongue-in-cheek blow-up of the official Recording 
Industry Assn. of America's voluntary parental warning sticker: "WARNING, 
