<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LONGER HOURS FOR FARMERS MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hermosa Beach's weekly open-air Farmers Market, at 13th Street and Hermosa 
Avenue, has been authorized to open 30 minutes earlier each Friday and close an 
hour later. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager Kevin Northcraft said Tuesday that residents requested the 
extended hours to make it easier to shop for the market's fresh produce during 
lunch breaks. 
</P>
<P>
The market, which has been open from 12:30 p.m. to 3:30 p.m., will open at noon 
and close at 4:30 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
