<TEXT>
<P>
County supervisors have ordered an investigation into the alleged misuse of 
county personnel and equipment in the Public Works Department. 
</P>
<P>
Supervisor Mike Antonovich called for the probe after published reports 
indicated that one foreman was suspended for his alleged actions, but was not 
fired because others had not been punished for similar actions in the past. 
</P>
<P>
Larry Parrish, a foreman in the Pasadena shop where workers allegedly built 
boat racks, fishing-lure molds and other items for his personal use, was 
suspended for 30 days. 
