<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Billy Kranz: Moorpark 
</P>
<P>
Soccer: Midfielder 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore: 5-foot-7, 145 
</P>
<P>
There is no shortage of players who excel on the undefeated Moorpark College 
soccer team, but Coach Frank Parodi says that Billy Kranz stands out from the 
rest. 
</P>
<P>
"I feel he's really the spark plug and the mainstay," Parodi said. 
</P>
<P>
"On the field, he's magic. He's not quick, but he's explosive." 
</P>
<P>
The team's leading scorer, Kranz had a goal nine days ago in a 3-0 win over 
Bakersfield, a goal and an assist in a 4-1 win Friday against Oxnard and two 
assists Tuesday in a 9-2 trouncing of Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark (10-0-0, 5-0-0 in Western State Conference play) has allowed only 
seven goals all season, but the Raiders had to play about 20 minutes without a 
banged-up Kranz in a match against Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
"Then, when he went in, boom, things just changed," Parodi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
