<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS: RAGIN' CAJUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A little bit of the Louisiana bayou will be transplanted to Agoura Hills 
Friday, when the "Cajun Occasion" festival kicks off at 3 p.m. with enough food 
and entertainment to last all weekend. 
</P>
<P>
The event is a fund-raiser for Fair Share Inc., an Agoura Hills-based 
organization dedicated to training disabled people interested in entering the 
computer field. 
</P>
<P>
More than 31 musical acts -- playing Dixieland, blues, jazz and zydeco -- and 
comedians will perform continuously through Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Friday's entertainment will continue until 11 p.m., and Saturday and Sunday 
events will be held from 10 a.m. to 11 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Cajun-Creole food fanciers can get their fill of gumbo, etoufee, chicken 
creole, jambalaya and crawfish, some of which will be prepared by chefs from 
New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
The event site will be at the corner of Agoura and Kanan roads. Admission for 
each day is $3. For more information, call 496-1111. 
</P>
</TEXT>
