<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: WEST COVINA; 
</P>
<P>
WOODGATE DRIVE BARRICADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Woodgate Drive will be barricaded permanently just west of Greenborough Place, 
the City Council decided. 
</P>
<P>
The street was temporarily blocked last November, after residents complained 
that motorists were speeding down Woodgate to avoid the intersection of Amar 
Road and Azusa Avenue. Because the temporary blockade significantly reduced 
traffic, residents asked for permanent closure. 
</P>
<P>
About 100 people, most backing the closing, came to Monday's council hearing. 
"Before I was living in a freeway, now I'm living in a neighborhood," Frank 
Anselmini said. 
</P>
<P>
But two people who live nearby said closing Woodgate would cause traffic 
congestion on their streets. 
</P>
<P>
Interim City Manager Harry Thomas estimated the cost of closing the street and 
forming cul-de-sacs on both sides at $29,857. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
