<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
3 FIREFIGHTERS TO BE HIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite the recommendation of the recent municipal audit, the City Council last 
week sided with Fire Chief Bart Carroll and unanimously approved the hiring of 
three firefighters. 
</P>
<P>
The three positions had been in the 1990-91 budget, but the audit by Hughes, 
Heiss &amp; Associates urged that a battalion chief or captain be hired instead 
to bolster administration and training. 
</P>
<P>
Carroll argued that the firefighters were a higher priority because the 
department has been short-handed in its response to structure fires. 
</P>
<P>
Other audit recommendations that have been implemented: 
</P>
<P>
* Police have increased hours of coverage by parking control officers and have 
started talks with San Marino on a joint dispatch center and with Pasadena on a 
possible jail-use contract. 
</P>
<P>
* The Planning Department will hire an additional associate planner and 
increase zoning enforcement by the building inspector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
