<TEXT>
<P>
Yields on Notes Rise: Yields on seven-year Treasury notes rose at auction to 
the highest level since April, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
The average yield was 8.76%, up from 8.57% at the last auction on July 11. It 
was the highest rate since seven-year notes averaged 9.39% on April 12, 1989. 
The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8.75% with each $10,000 in face 
value selling for $9,994.80. A total of $8.5 billion in notes were sold out of 
bids totaling $15 billion. 
</P>
