<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
FLAG ESSAY CONTEST OPEN TO 6TH-GRADERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixth-grade students in the Saddleback school system have been invited to 
compete for prizes in an essay contest titled "Why We Should Honor Our Flag." 
</P>
<P>
The contest is part of the California/Hawaii Elks Essay contest, which will see 
students from both states compete for local and state prizes, according to Joe 
Urban, an Elks spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
The Mission Viejo-Saddleback Valley Elks Lodge will award $75, $50 and $25 
prizes to the top three boys' essays and the top three girls' essays. 
</P>
<P>
Entry forms are available from Dale Smith at the Mission Viejo Elks, 25092 
Marquerite Parkway, Mission Viejo, 92692. The deadline to enter the contest is 
Nov. 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
