<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR UCI PLAYERS SURVIVE QUALIFYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four UC Irvine tennis players advanced on Wednesday to the main draw of the 
Rolex-ITCA Southern California Regional championships at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Courtney Weichsel, Maggie Powers, Michelle Foster and Biljana Korac each won 
two qualifying matches to move into the 64-player main draw, which starts today 
at UCI. Ali Yoshimoto, who automatically qualified for the main draw, will play 
Barbara Thompson of Arizona State at 9:30 a.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
Two Anteater doubles teams, Yoshimoto-Foster and Kelly Goldsborough-Jennifer 
Mazgedian, also won qualifying matches. 
</P>
