POLICE FIRE ON RETURNING SOVIETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet police fired machine-guns at three families in four cars that failed to 
stop at a road checkpoint returning from a trip to the West, the Communist 
Party daily Pravda said today. 
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old boy was injured and the cars were riddled with bullets in the 
nighttime incident near the Ural Mountains city of Chelyabinsk. The families, 
driving foreign-made cars from Germany to Kazakhstan, said they ignored an 
order to stop because they mistook the police for roadside bandits. 
</P>
