<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japanese baseball fans will get their chance to toast Cecil Fielder, the newest 
member of the 50-homer club, now that the Detroit Tigers have given their 
approval. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Greenberg, deputy commissioner of baseball, announced in September that 
Fielder would be part of the all-star team sent to Japan for a string of eight 
exhibition games in November. But Tigers General Manager Bill Lajoie said the 
commissioner's office failed to get permission from the club to include 
Fielder. Lajoie has since given Fielder permission to play in the tour. 
</P>
<P>
A photograph of Fielder, idolized in Japan since his stint last year with the 
Hanshin Tigers, appears on the tour's program. 
