<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
ABC PLANS A DOLLY GOOD HOLIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PIGEON FORGE, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dolly Parton is back home this week filming a Christmas TV special that will 
include scenes at the singer's childhood home and the church where she 
worshiped as a young woman. 
</P>
<P>
The special, "Dolly Parton . . . Christmas at Home," will feature a celebration 
of the Christmas season with Parton and members of her family, said Barbara 
Headla, marketing manager for Dollywood, Parton's theme park. 
</P>
<P>
Shooting was to start today and is scheduled to wind up Tuesday. The program 
will be aired on ABC about a week before Christmas, Headla said. 
</P>
<P>
Parton has also recorded a radio special that will be picked up by 500 radio 
stations, the Armed Forces Radio Network, the British Broadcasting Corp. and 
the Voice of America, Headla said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Dolly Parton 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
